place.name: CROWNTHORPE
place.gazetteerText: CROWNTHORPE, a parish in Forehoe district, Norfolk; on the river Yare and the Norfolk railway, 2½ miles N W of Wymondham. Post town, Wymondham. Acres, 696. Real property, £1, 604. Pop., 97. Houses, 18. The property is divided among a few. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £155.* Patron, Earl of Kimberley. The church is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
